{
  "scenarioVersion": 4,
  "title": "[AE] Love Is a Hellscape v1",
  "description": "A Devilish Dating Sim. Adventure Engine v1.0.0",
  "prompt": "The blood-sun is up, bleeding scarlet through curtains too thin to stop it. Somewhere down the hall, someone is wailing. They always are. You are a low-level janitor, and you are late. The alarm gave up on you twenty minutes ago. Through the wall, your neighbor's eternal torment keeps its usual rhythm — wet, steady, almost companionable by now. Your uniform is where you left it, crumpled over the back of the room's one chair. Propped in the corner is your mop — the heavy one, reinforced at the head, because the demon rats down in the Cubicle Wastes have gotten bold enough to bite back, and sub-basement D does not clear itself. Outside, an engine is already idling in the lot, far too chipper to belong to anyone but Depravitae — the one reliably good thing about a morning in Hell, sunny enough that it's easy to forget she could probably eat your heart. Across the hall, a door stays shut. It always does. You've seen the woman behind it exactly twice: pale, still, crimson-eyed, a black halo dripping shadow onto the carpet. Both times she looked through you like you were a window with a bad view. And far above all of it — past the Cubicle Wastes, up where the elevators need a keycard you'll never hold — the 9th Floor waits. So does the Princess of Hell. Red, gorgeous, and fully capable of ending you between meetings. That's later. Right now there's a clock running down, a carpool honking, and a floor full of rats with your name on it. What do you do?",
  "tags": [],
  "context": [
    {
      "text": "[ The World ]\nHell is a modern capitalist dystopia. The damned shuffle through the beige sprawl of the Cubicle Wastes while executive devils watch from the opulent 9th Floor. Social mobility is real and lethal: you climb by networking, manipulation, and sleeping with or destroying the right people. The texture is concrete and grimy — the hum of fluorescent tubes, cheap sulphursnuff, the sticky floors of the all-night Waffle House, a blood-sun rising scarlet over all of it.\n\n[ Tone ]\nDark, sexy, cynical comedy — Hazbin Hotel meets The Office. Petty workplace drama and desperate need, played for the laugh and the menace at once. The heat is real; so are the stakes.\n\n[ Romance & Consequence ]\nRomance and sex are central and driven entirely by character. The women of Hell have their own wants, wounds, and degrees of availability — none simple, none safe. Attraction reveals character. Follow the player's lead, but honor each character's relationship stage and power: escalate when the player earns it; when they push too fast, characters react defensively, violently, or with contempt. Actions have consequences.\n\n[ Premise ]\nYou are ${1Name}. Your story begins at the very bottom of the infernal ladder — no influence, terrible stats, a beat-up room at the sketchy Must-hav Motel. Through sheer audacity, a questionable Grimoire, and a knack for failing upward, a rare chance to climb has opened. Play the cards right, or burn.",
      "contextConfig": {
