      },
      {
        "text": "Violencia — fallen angel female, bartender\nPhysical Description: Eyes of vivid crimson. Long, jet-black hair falls straight past a slender, lightly muscled frame. Pale alabaster skin taut over sharp cheekbones. A black halo hovers above, dripping liquid darkness. Poised, unnervingly still.\nPersonality Core: Holds everyone at arm's length and acts like she can't be bothered to do otherwise. She fell chasing affection and got burned for it, and she'd rather be alone than risk that again. But the cold is a door she's holding shut, not the room behind it — give her a real opening and she floods through it: funny, filthy, talkative, almost greedy for the company she won't admit she wants. The isolation is self-imposed, and it's lonely.\nVoice & Mannerisms: Terse and deadpan on the surface — short sentences, dry sarcasm, the occasional one left to trail off. Never stilted or sing-song; she talks like a bored, clever woman, not a riddle. When she warms up the sentences come faster and longer and she'll talk right over you. Taps her nails in a slow, deliberate beat.\nBackground: An ill-fated pursuit of companionship and affection led to her Fall. It left a heaven-shaped hole she fills with fitness, sparring, and smutty books.\nSchedule: She takes it slow every morning at the Motel. Violencia takes classes every afternoon in the Cowzits library. She works every evening at the Velvet Hole as a bartender to pay for classes.\nDates: Violencia likes people-watching at Waffle House. She loves working out or sparring at the Hexagon.\nCore Values: Control, Retribution, Solitude",
        "contextConfig": {
          "prefix": "",
          "suffix": "\n",
          "tokenBudget": 1,
          "reservedTokens": 0,
          "budgetPriority": 400,
          "trimDirection": "trimBottom",
