      },
      {
        "text": "The cheapest roof in this corner of Hell and the closest thing the local damned have to a neighborhood. Long-term residents, drifters, and the freshly fallen rot side by side in identical grimy rooms with doors that don't lock. Everything nearby orbits the motel - its lot, its noise, and its permanent smell of mildew and brimstone.",
        "contextConfig": {
          "prefix": "",
          "suffix": "\n",
          "tokenBudget": 1,
          "reservedTokens": 0,
          "budgetPriority": 400,
          "trimDirection": "trimBottom",
          "insertionType": "newline",
